      <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">We go deeper into exactly how this works on our <a href="/how-we-work-with-artists/" class="text-link">how we work with artists</a> page, and into what platforms will and won't accept in <a href="/blog/is-ai-music-allowed-on-spotify/" class="text-link">is AI music allowed on Spotify?</a></p>
    </section>

    <section id="conclusion" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <h2 style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Conclusion</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">AI music can absolutely be ethical - when the model is trained with consent and there's genuine human authorship in the result. Both are choices: the tool's makers choose how the model is built, and you choose how you use it. Pick tools on the licensed side, do real creative work, and you have nothing to apologize for.</p>
